1
00:01:07,920 --> 00:01:10,319
Plot 7 covers 250,000 square meters

2
00:01:10,680 --> 00:01:12,239
Starting bid: 1.8 billion yuan

3
00:01:12,239 --> 00:01:14,120
Each bid increment: minimum 5 million yuan

4
00:01:14,439 --> 00:01:15,439
The auction begins

5
00:01:16,239 --> 00:01:16,799
Any bids?

6
00:01:18,239 --> 00:01:19,120
1.8 billion

7
00:01:19,519 --> 00:01:20,400
Remote and overpriced

8
00:01:20,719 --> 00:01:21,560
Whoever buys it loses

9
00:01:23,079 --> 00:01:23,719
1.8 billion

10
00:01:26,840 --> 00:01:27,840
1.8 billion yuan

11
00:01:27,879 --> 00:01:29,599
Wanhe Group bids 1.8 billion yuan

12
00:01:29,959 --> 00:01:30,879
Any higher bids?

13
00:01:33,519 --> 00:01:35,000
Any higher offers?

14
00:01:35,439 --> 00:01:36,640
1.8 billion yuan, going once

15
00:01:40,359 --> 00:01:41,239
Hey, Yifan

16
00:01:41,799 --> 00:01:43,000
Have you completely lost your mind today?

17
00:01:43,280 --> 00:01:44,799
Is this dump really worth that much?

18
00:01:46,079 --> 00:01:46,760
Brother

19
00:01:47,879 --> 00:01:48,760
Trust me

20
00:01:49,599 --> 00:01:51,120
1.8 billion yuan, going twice

21
00:01:51,959 --> 00:01:54,319
What are Xiao Yifan and He Junjie up to?

22
00:01:54,959 --> 00:01:56,400
Plot 7 is so desolate

23
00:01:56,680 --> 00:01:58,239
It has no development value at all

24
00:01:58,879 --> 00:02:00,560
Why would they buy it?

25
00:02:01,359 --> 00:02:02,799
1.8 billion yuan, going three times

26
00:02:03,159 --> 00:02:03,920
Sold!

27
00:02:04,000 --> 00:02:05,120
Congratulations to Wanhe Group

28
00:02:10,919 --> 00:02:13,280
Thank you all for the spirited bidding.

29
00:02:13,280 --> 00:02:15,639
Today's auction concludes successfully

30
00:02:16,120 --> 00:02:18,240
Would the winning bidders please

31
00:02:18,360 --> 00:02:20,080
come up to sign the confirmation document

32
00:02:20,240 --> 00:02:21,080
Please come forward

33
00:02:25,879 --> 00:02:27,560
Mr. Xiao, Mr. Xiao

34
00:02:35,479 --> 00:02:36,400
Thank you

35
00:02:45,360 --> 00:02:47,360
A bold move, with remarkable vision

36
00:02:47,840 --> 00:02:48,919
Thank you

37
00:03:07,479 --> 00:03:08,520
Come on, Mr. Fang and Mr. Xiao.

38
00:03:08,520 --> 00:03:10,759
Let's take a photo over here.

39
00:03:15,120 --> 00:03:15,759
Mr. Xiao.

40
00:03:16,240 --> 00:03:19,840
I didn't expect you'd be so set on Plot 7.

41
00:03:20,439 --> 00:03:21,159
Mr. Fang.

42
00:03:21,840 --> 00:03:23,439
Every plot has its own unique value.

43
00:03:23,719 --> 00:03:25,159
Like fresh graduates leaving school,

44
00:03:25,719 --> 00:03:26,879
who can really tell

45
00:03:27,439 --> 00:03:28,479
which one will be the dark horse?

46
00:03:29,080 --> 00:03:29,599
Fine.

47
00:03:30,360 --> 00:03:32,120
I'll see how this dark horse of yours

48
00:03:32,479 --> 00:03:33,560
takes flight.

49
00:03:34,840 --> 00:03:36,960
Mr. Fang, Mr. Xiao, please look here.

50
00:03:39,639 --> 00:03:40,719
Good.

51
00:03:47,479 --> 00:03:48,319
Mr. Fang.

52
00:03:48,560 --> 00:03:50,360
Fang Group paid such a high premium

53
00:03:50,360 --> 00:03:51,439
to win Plot 6.

54
00:03:51,439 --> 00:03:53,680
How do you plan to develop it?

55
00:03:53,680 --> 00:03:56,479
Winning Plot 6 means a great deal to our company.

56
00:03:56,719 --> 00:04:00,240
We plan to build a large complex

57
00:04:00,240 --> 00:04:01,360
combining commercial and residential spaces.

58
00:04:01,560 --> 00:04:04,840
To help boost Loujiang City's economy.

59
00:04:05,439 --> 00:04:07,120
Alright, thank you, Mr. Fang.

60
00:04:13,439 --> 00:04:14,479
Yifan.

61
00:04:17,680 --> 00:04:19,639
Congratulations on winning Plot 7.

62
00:04:20,319 --> 00:04:21,720
It may not be as valuable as Plot 6,

63
00:04:22,079 --> 00:04:25,120
but I know your every move has a reason.

64
00:04:26,399 --> 00:04:27,160
I have faith in you.

65
00:04:30,639 --> 00:04:31,759
Thank you for the kind words, President Su.

66
00:04:34,720 --> 00:04:39,639
Getting me drunk almost cost me the bid.

67
00:04:42,759 --> 00:04:43,399
Yifan.

68
00:04:43,920 --> 00:04:44,759
Yifan.

69
00:04:46,959 --> 00:04:47,680
Sorry,

70
00:04:48,079 --> 00:04:49,279
I have other matters to attend to.

71
00:05:14,959 --> 00:05:16,000
Congratulations, Mr. Xiao.

72
00:05:16,120 --> 00:05:17,600
We'll have chances to work together.

73
00:05:17,720 --> 00:05:19,639
You know what my wife is capable of.

74
00:05:22,079 --> 00:05:23,279
We'll talk when the chance arises.

75
00:05:25,160 --> 00:05:26,399
Then I won't keep you two any longer.

76
00:05:26,399 --> 00:05:27,879
My wife and I have matters to attend to.

77
00:05:38,319 --> 00:05:39,000
Crooked businessman.

78
00:05:39,759 --> 00:05:41,199
Seeing him reminds me of the site accident.

79
00:05:41,879 --> 00:05:44,600
Who knows how many Fang Bing has ruined.

80
00:05:46,680 --> 00:05:47,079
Also,

81
00:05:47,079 --> 00:05:48,279
that wall on the south side.

82
00:05:48,680 --> 00:05:49,839
Do you even know what you're doing?

83
00:05:50,279 --> 00:05:51,759
Yes, yes, I'll fix it.

84
00:05:52,240 --> 00:05:53,399
The south wall, right.

85
00:05:56,240 --> 00:05:57,839
This guy's here again.

86
00:06:00,800 --> 00:06:01,680
Handle him.

87
00:06:08,079 --> 00:06:08,639
You're here.

88
00:06:10,040 --> 00:06:12,199
Manager Xiao, have a smoke.

89
00:06:15,319 --> 00:06:15,800
Manager Xiao.

90
00:06:16,519 --> 00:06:17,279
Have a cigarette.

91
00:06:17,319 --> 00:06:18,839
It's so hot, let's grab a drink over there.

92
00:06:21,040 --> 00:06:22,279
This batch of angle steel is wrong.

93
00:06:22,879 --> 00:06:24,160
The thickness and material are both off.

94
00:06:24,879 --> 00:06:26,199
Didn't you notice?

95
00:06:26,199 --> 00:06:27,160
When the materials arrived,

96
00:06:27,319 --> 00:06:28,279
didn't you inspect them?

97
00:06:28,959 --> 00:06:31,959
Manager Xiao, these are for the supports.

98
00:06:32,160 --> 00:06:34,399
I haven't reported to Engineer Li yet.

99
00:06:34,639 --> 00:06:35,399
Don't worry.

100
00:06:35,560 --> 00:06:37,199
The quality is definitely fine.

101
00:06:37,199 --> 00:06:39,199
At most, it's just non-standard.

102
00:06:39,680 --> 00:06:41,040
Do you know what happens

103
00:06:41,360 --> 00:06:42,920
when the material isn't thick enough?

104
00:06:43,439 --> 00:06:44,920
It can cause a collapse, you understand?

105
00:06:45,759 --> 00:06:47,759
Can you bear that responsibility?

106
00:06:48,439 --> 00:06:49,360
Or tell me,

107
00:06:49,759 --> 00:06:50,639
which of you can?

108
00:06:51,319 --> 00:06:52,879
Stop working, all of you!

109
00:06:55,040 --> 00:06:57,519
This might just be a batch issue.

110
00:06:57,639 --> 00:06:59,879
I'll replace it with proper materials ASAP.

111
00:07:06,040 --> 00:07:07,519
This isn't a batch issue.

112
00:07:07,759 --> 00:07:09,639
This is a serious safety hazard.

113
00:07:11,639 --> 00:07:14,120
Return all substandard materials at once.

114
00:07:14,800 --> 00:07:17,079
And tear down everything already installed.

115
00:07:17,639 --> 00:07:19,120
We can't do that, Manager Xiao.

116
00:07:19,240 --> 00:07:20,879
If we tear all this down,

117
00:07:20,879 --> 00:07:22,040
Mr. Fang's losses will be huge.

118
00:07:22,040 --> 00:07:23,199
I really can't take the blame for that.

119
00:07:23,360 --> 00:07:24,000
How about this...

120
00:07:24,240 --> 00:07:25,879
Look, Manager Xiao.

121
00:07:26,000 --> 00:07:27,040
Take this.

122
00:07:27,160 --> 00:07:28,839
I'll treat you to dinner tonight.

123
00:07:28,839 --> 00:07:30,160
Don't try that crap with me.

124
00:07:31,680 --> 00:07:33,079
Site safety comes first.

125
00:07:33,279 --> 00:07:35,079
Get someone here to inspect right now.

126
00:07:35,319 --> 00:07:36,240
Find out exactly how much was used.

127
00:07:36,519 --> 00:07:37,759
Tear it all down immediately.

128
00:07:37,759 --> 00:07:38,800
Li Yao.

129
00:07:39,240 --> 00:07:40,759
Stay on site and keep a close watch.

130
00:07:40,959 --> 00:07:41,680
Until the materials are hauled away,

131
00:07:42,040 --> 00:07:42,720
no construction allowed.

132
00:07:43,199 --> 00:07:44,160
Don't worry, Manager Xiao.

133
00:07:44,439 --> 00:07:45,639
I'll supervise them closely.

134
00:08:02,439 --> 00:08:03,600
What's this supposed to mean?

135
00:08:04,079 --> 00:08:04,720
Think it's too little?

136
00:08:05,600 --> 00:08:06,720
Once this project is done,

137
00:08:06,759 --> 00:08:07,720
I'll hand you a bigger envelope.

138
00:08:08,639 --> 00:08:09,439
No way.

139
00:08:09,560 --> 00:08:10,319
The company has rules.

140
00:08:10,319 --> 00:08:11,480
If I'm caught, I'm finished.

141
00:08:11,759 --> 00:08:12,800
You don't tell, I don't tell.

142
00:08:12,800 --> 00:08:13,319
Who would ever know?

143
00:08:16,000 --> 00:08:17,079
Nothing's gonna happen, right?

144
00:08:17,399 --> 00:08:18,399
This batch of defective materials,

145
00:08:18,399 --> 00:08:19,519
I can install them all in one night.

146
00:08:19,879 --> 00:08:21,600
Trust me, stick with me.

147
00:08:22,120 --> 00:08:23,160
You'll make a fortune.

148
00:08:25,040 --> 00:08:25,639
Get to work!

149
00:08:26,240 --> 00:08:27,279
Move it!

150
00:08:28,000 --> 00:08:30,759
No one leaves until it's done tonight.

151
00:08:41,159 --> 00:08:42,279
This Fang Bing,

152
00:08:42,919 --> 00:08:44,080
we need to be careful with him.

153
00:08:47,440 --> 00:08:48,840
As for Plot 7,

154
00:08:48,840 --> 00:08:50,159
the future plans will be impressive.

155
00:08:50,799 --> 00:08:51,720
I'll fill you in back at the office.

156
00:08:51,960 --> 00:08:52,840
Mr. Xiao.

157
00:08:53,320 --> 00:08:54,679
There was an incident on the way.

158
00:08:55,039 --> 00:08:55,720
My apologies.

159
00:08:55,799 --> 00:08:56,799
For delaying your bid.

160
00:08:58,360 --> 00:08:59,399
Here you go.

161
00:09:00,600 --> 00:09:01,399
You're too late.

162
00:09:02,159 --> 00:09:02,879
A bit late for that.

163
00:09:03,279 --> 00:09:04,559
What the hell's the point now?

164
00:09:05,320 --> 00:09:06,039
I'm sorry.

165
00:09:06,759 --> 00:09:07,840
I had a car accident.

166
00:09:08,960 --> 00:09:10,039
Get your injuries treated first.

167
00:09:10,440 --> 00:09:11,159
Whatever the issue,

168
00:09:11,360 --> 00:09:12,320
take it up with Chairman Zheng later.

169
00:09:19,679 --> 00:09:20,919
Don't act so high and mighty.

170
00:09:21,559 --> 00:09:23,039
Let's see how you clean this up.

171
00:09:34,279 --> 00:09:35,360
We lost Plot 6.

172
00:09:35,360 --> 00:09:36,440
How do we explain to Chairman Zheng?

173
00:09:37,799 --> 00:09:39,360
I already discussed it with Chairman Zheng.

174
00:09:39,480 --> 00:09:40,440
We never intended to win it.

175
00:09:41,039 --> 00:09:41,480
What?

176
00:09:42,480 --> 00:09:42,919
Chairman Zheng.

177
00:09:43,559 --> 00:09:44,679
Drive up the price of Plot 6,

178
00:09:44,840 --> 00:09:46,799
but what we really wanted was Plot 7.

179
00:09:47,279 --> 00:09:47,759
Got it.

180
00:09:48,960 --> 00:09:51,200
Phase One of Wanhe Mansion is selling well,

181
00:09:51,320 --> 00:09:54,039
but that area's market is near saturation.

182
00:09:54,120 --> 00:09:56,519
That'll seriously impact Phase Two sales.

183
00:09:56,879 --> 00:09:59,159
So I deliberately leaked word

184
00:09:59,159 --> 00:10:00,480
that we were determined to win it.

185
00:10:00,480 --> 00:10:01,799
but actually just to drive up the price.

186
00:10:01,960 --> 00:10:05,559
By then, bread and flour will cost about the same.

187
00:10:05,840 --> 00:10:07,480
Think we'll still struggle to sell?

188
00:10:08,759 --> 00:10:10,120
You're so sly!

189
00:10:10,720 --> 00:10:13,320
I feel the market's running too hot right now.

190
00:10:13,759 --> 00:10:16,320
I think the government, like in past years,

191
00:10:16,320 --> 00:10:18,000
will roll out policies to cool it down.

192
00:10:18,559 --> 00:10:20,080
If we took Plot 6,

193
00:10:20,120 --> 00:10:21,559
the development cost would be too high,

194
00:10:21,919 --> 00:10:23,120
and the risk even greater.

195
00:10:23,519 --> 00:10:24,320
I see.

196
00:10:24,679 --> 00:10:26,480
But Plot 7 is so far from downtown,

197
00:10:26,480 --> 00:10:28,120
and the project's so big. How can we pull it off?

198
00:10:29,320 --> 00:10:30,519
It's precisely because of its scale

199
00:10:30,759 --> 00:10:32,399
that there's more room for development.

200
00:10:32,879 --> 00:10:34,399
I researched and ran the numbers.

201
00:10:34,600 --> 00:10:35,840
The location may be remote,

202
00:10:36,000 --> 00:10:38,440
but the surroundings are beautiful, with hills and water.

203
00:10:38,759 --> 00:10:40,519
We'll develop it in phases.

204
00:10:40,559 --> 00:10:41,240
Phase One

205
00:10:41,440 --> 00:10:43,159
will be Loujiang City's top luxury estate.

206
00:10:43,200 --> 00:10:44,720
The wealthy won't mind the distance.

207
00:10:46,399 --> 00:10:47,320
Way to go, brother.

208
00:10:50,159 --> 00:10:52,080
I knew you never fight an unprepared battle.

209
00:10:52,480 --> 00:10:54,159
Going the luxury development route,

210
00:10:55,200 --> 00:10:56,320
it'll definitely sell out fast.

211
00:10:56,879 --> 00:10:58,120
Build large-unit townhouses,

212
00:10:58,240 --> 00:11:00,480
then hire a celebrity brand ambassador.

213
00:11:00,600 --> 00:11:01,720
Promote it properly.

214
00:11:02,120 --> 00:11:02,720
Also,

215
00:11:02,840 --> 00:11:05,320
We can also pitch a local tourism project.

216
00:11:05,919 --> 00:11:07,399
to expand our company's business lines.

217
00:11:07,679 --> 00:11:08,679
You should've said so earlier!

218
00:11:08,919 --> 00:11:10,080
You had me worried sick.

219
00:11:10,759 --> 00:11:11,399
Let's go.

220
00:11:13,200 --> 00:11:14,639
Losing Plot 6,

221
00:11:14,639 --> 00:11:15,639
I want an explanation.

222
00:11:16,200 --> 00:11:17,039
It was President Han.

223
00:11:17,159 --> 00:11:18,600
The temporary authorization was delivered late.

224
00:11:19,360 --> 00:11:20,879
How could you fail at something so simple?

225
00:11:21,399 --> 00:11:23,240
Chairman Zheng, I'm truly sorry.

226
00:11:23,600 --> 00:11:25,440
You see, I was in a car accident.

227
00:11:26,159 --> 00:11:27,000
It's all my fault.

228
00:11:28,159 --> 00:11:28,799
Are you all right?

229
00:11:29,639 --> 00:11:30,399
I'm fine.

230
00:11:31,000 --> 00:11:32,200
I just missed the auction,

231
00:11:32,919 --> 00:11:35,240
costing the company Plot 6.

232
00:11:35,519 --> 00:11:36,279
Chairman Zheng,

233
00:11:36,799 --> 00:11:38,600
I really can't bear this loss.

234
00:11:39,879 --> 00:11:40,440
All right, all right.

235
00:11:40,919 --> 00:11:41,559
Get to the hospital, quick.

236
00:11:42,600 --> 00:11:43,279
Okay.

237
00:11:53,519 --> 00:11:54,039
Chairman Zheng,

238
00:11:54,519 --> 00:11:56,399
To keep you from getting Plot 6,

239
00:11:56,399 --> 00:11:57,559
Han Lin paid quite a heavy price.

240
00:11:59,200 --> 00:12:00,200
You guessed it right.

241
00:12:00,200 --> 00:12:02,200
Han Lin is definitely up to something.

242
00:12:02,759 --> 00:12:03,840
You've got a sharp mind.

243
00:12:04,399 --> 00:12:05,360
On par with Hawthorne.

244
00:12:06,879 --> 00:12:08,759
Han Lin is as ruthless as ever.

245
00:12:10,080 --> 00:12:11,080
That construction site accident seven years ago,

246
00:12:11,480 --> 00:12:12,159
could he have been involved too?
